          {
            "commit": "b4d4a448b2ed93a8bc73db81bbf9c8ba08250e3a",
            "subject": "LU-7349 lfsck: skip auto resume lfsck when mount"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-12-09 14:27:05.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-01-05 00:49:12.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-7210 o2iblnd: take extra refcount in kiblnd_connreq_done",
        "message": "LU-7210 o2iblnd: take extra refcount in kiblnd_connreq_done\n\nrefcount taken by cmid is not reliable after kiblnd_connreq_done\nreleased the glock because this connection is visible to other\nthreads, another thread can find and close this connection right\nafter kiblnd_connreq_done released the glock, if kiblnd_cm_callback\nfor RDMA_CM_EVENT_DISCONNECTED is called, it can release the\nconnection refcount taken by cmid. It means the connection could be\ndestroyed before kiblnd_connreq_done() finish operations on it.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ic49b63551c13abc8c874732de5fd4ea5cef4c6b7\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/17527\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Doug Oucharek <doug.s.oucharek@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nTested-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
